CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 18, 1953, pg. 2 reads: "Blind Mother Loses "Eyes"...son commits suicide - Harris Photo"...The tragedy that took away the "eyes" of Mrs. Tillie Jones, 135 Trent Street, occurred early Monday, April 13, in Centre Avenue police station. Her son, Charley W. Jones, committed suicide."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Tillie Jones, wearing plaid dress with light colored collar, tuning dial on radio, in home on 135 Trent Street
